'''Natalia Nogulich''' (born [[October 1]], [[1950s#1950|1950]]) is an American actress who has performed in theatre, television and film. She was the voice of [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] in the [[Return of the Jedi (radio)|''Return of the Jedi'' radio drama]].<ref>[[Return of the Jedi (radio)|''Return of the Jedi'' radio drama]]</ref> Nogulich spells her first name "'''Natalija'''", but in many of her credits it is spelled "Natalia".<ref name="imdb" />

Nogulich was born in Chicago and began her career in local theatre companies. She studied in Illinois, Spain, Italy, and New York. One of her first TV roles was in 1980 in an episode of ''Lou Grant,'' starring her future ''Return of the Jedi'' co-performer [[Ed Asner]].<ref name="imdb" /> Her time in New York led to Broadway roles in ''Hurlyburly'' and ''The Iceman Cometh'' in 1984 and 1985.<ref name="ibdb">{{WebCite |url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-cast-staff/natalia-nogulich-74427 |text=Natalia Nogulich |work=Internet Broadway Database |archivedate=20230407055803}}</ref><ref name="bio">{{WebCite|url=https://natalijanogulich.com/biography|text=Biography|work=NatalijaNogulich.com|archivedate=20230925185253}}</ref> She has been a steady presence on television since the 1980s. Her best-known role was  [[MemoryAlpha:Alynna Nechayev|Vice Admiral Alynna Nechayev]] in four episodes of [[MemoryAlpha:Star Trek: The Next Generation|''Star Trek: The Next Generation'']] and two episodes of [[MemoryAlpha:Star Trek: Deep Space Nine|''Star Trek: Deep Space Nine'']]. She also appeared on episodes of series such as ''24'', ''Bones'' and ''The West Wing''.<ref name="imdb" /> 

Besides her acting work, Nogulich has directed productions in Illinois and the District of Columbia and has written a novel, ''One Woman's War.'' She has taught theatre classes in a number of institutions. She now lives again in Chicago.<ref name="bio" />

